The paper discusses the use of Restricted Boltzmann Machines (RBM) as classifiers or generative models, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The focus of the paper is on evaluating the quality of generative RBMs through the estimation of test log-likelihood, which involves image processing and computer vision techniques (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of various estimation methods, which involves statistical and numerical analysis (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves the use of algorithms for computation, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
